ğŸ§  What Are Hooks?

Hooks are special functions in React that let you:

* Use **state**
* Use **lifecycle features**
* Reuse logic
* Avoid class components

ğŸ“Œ Hooks work only in **functional components**
ğŸ“Œ Introduced in React 16.8

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Rules of Hooks (Very Important â­)

1ï¸âƒ£ Call hooks only at top level
2ï¸âƒ£ Call hooks only inside React functions
3ï¸âƒ£ Do not use inside loops or conditions

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· 1ï¸âƒ£ useState Hook (Deep Dive)

Purpose:

Used to manage **state in functional components**

---

ğŸ§¾ Syntax

```jsx
const [state, setState] = useState(initialValue);
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ” Counter Example

```jsx
import { useState } from "react";

function Counter() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return (
    <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>
      {count}
    </button>
  );
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Updating state â†’ re-render

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ” Functional Update

```jsx
setCount(prev => prev + 1);
```

âœ” Best for multiple updates

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· 2ï¸âƒ£ useEffect Hook (Deep Dive)

Purpose:

Used for **side effects**

Examples:

* API calls
* Timers
* Subscriptions
* DOM manipulation

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§¾ Basic Syntax

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  // code here
}, [dependencies]);
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· useEffect Variations

1ï¸âƒ£ Run Once (On Mount)

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  console.log("Component mounted");
}, []);
```

ğŸ“Œ Empty dependency array

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2ï¸âƒ£ Run On State Change

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  console.log("Count changed");
}, [count]);
```

ğŸ“Œ Runs when count changes

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

3ï¸âƒ£ Run On Every Render

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  console.log("Every render");
});
```

ğŸ“Œ No dependency array

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· Cleanup Function

```jsx
useEffect(() => {
  const timer = setInterval(() => {
    console.log("Running...");
  }, 1000);

  return () => clearInterval(timer);
}, []);
```

ğŸ“Œ Cleanup prevents memory leaks

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· useRef Hook

Used to:

* Access DOM elements
* Store mutable values

```jsx
import { useRef } from "react";

function FocusInput() {
  const inputRef = useRef();

  return (
    <input ref={inputRef} />
  );
}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· useContext Hook

Used to access **global state**

```jsx
const value = useContext(MyContext);
```

ğŸ“Œ Avoids prop drilling

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· useMemo Hook

Used to optimize performance.

```jsx
const result = useMemo(() => {
  return expensiveCalculation(value);
}, [value]);
```

ğŸ“Œ Prevents unnecessary recalculation

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· useCallback Hook

Used to memoize functions.

```jsx
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  console.log("Clicked");
}, []);
```

ğŸ“Œ Prevents re-creation of functions

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  useEffect vs Lifecycle Methods

| Class Lifecycle      | useEffect Equivalent  |
| -------------------- | --------------------- |
| componentDidMount    | useEffect(..., [])    |
| componentDidUpdate   | useEffect(..., [dep]) |
| componentWillUnmount | Cleanup function      |

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âš ï¸ Common Hook Mistakes

âŒ Forgetting dependency array
âŒ Wrong dependencies
âŒ Updating state inside effect without condition
âŒ Using hooks inside loops
âŒ Infinite re-renders

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ’¡ Best Practices

âœ” Use functional components
âœ” Use useEffect carefully
âœ” Always clean up effects
âœ” Keep state minimal
âœ” Split logic into custom hooks

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  Real-World Use Cases

* Fetch API data
* Auto-refresh dashboard
* Dark mode toggle
* Authentication state
* Form handling
* Debouncing search input

